54th Avenue, east from 2nd Street. On the left are the Long Island Railroad yards and on the right the National Sugar Refining Company buildings (1928 map).

725447f-c.text:
54th Avenue, north side, west from 5th to 2nd Streets, showing the Long Island Railroad yards and the old Long Island City railroad station on 2nd Street. The station extends to Borden Avenue. Also shown, in view 2, is the railroad power house.
P. L. Sperr
